Power Action Words

1. Accelerate – to speed up progress  
   Example:  
   > “We need to accelerate the implementation of this strategy to stay ahead of our competitors.”

2. Thrive – to grow or develop successfully  
   Example:  
   > “Our team continues to thrive even in challenging market conditions.”

3. Facilitate – to make an action or process easier  
   Example:  
   > “I will facilitate the discussion to ensure everyone has a chance to contribute.”

4. Catalyze – to cause or accelerate a reaction  
   Example:  
   > “The new policy will catalyze the adoption of innovative practices across the department.”

5. Propel – to drive forward  
   Example:  
   > “This new marketing campaign will help propel our brand into new markets.”

6. Revitalize – to give new energy or strength  
   Example:  
   > “We need to revitalize our approach to customer service to boost client satisfaction.”

7. Perceive – to understand or interpret  
   Example: "It’s important to perceive changes in the market quickly to adapt our strategy."

8. Articulate – to express clearly  
   Example: "He was able to articulate the project goals effectively to the stakeholders."

9. Cultivate – to foster the growth of  
   Example: "We should cultivate relationships with key clients to ensure long-term success."

10. Formulate – to develop or create  
    Example: "We need to formulate a plan to address the feedback from our clients."

11. Consolidate – to combine into a more effective whole  
    Example: "We need to consolidate our resources to maximize efficiency."

12. Streamline – to make more efficient  
    Example: "We are looking to streamline our internal processes to reduce delays."

13. Empower – to give authority or power  
    Example: "Our goal is to empower team members to make decisions independently."

14. Delegate – to assign responsibility  
    Example: "I will delegate some of my tasks to ensure everything gets done on time."

15. Pivot – to change direction or strategy  
    Example: "We need to pivot our strategy based on the latest market trends."

16. Advocate – to publicly support  
    Example: "We should advocate for better employee benefits to improve morale."

17. Allocate – to distribute resources for a purpose  
    Example: "Let’s allocate more budget to research and development."

18. Foster – to promote the development of  
    Example: "Our goal is to foster a culture of continuous learning within the team."

19. Adapt – to adjust to new conditions  
    Example: "We need to adapt quickly to changes in customer preferences."

20. Reinforce – to strengthen or support  
    Example: "Let’s reinforce our core values during the next team meeting."

21. Validate – to confirm or prove accuracy  
    Example: "We need to validate these assumptions before moving forward with the plan."

22. Enforce – to compel compliance  
    Example: "We should enforce the new safety regulations across all departments."

23. Liaise – to establish a working relationship  
    Example: "I will liaise with the marketing team to ensure our messaging is aligned."

24. Align – to bring into cooperation or agreement  
    Example: "We need to align our objectives with the company’s overall mission."

25. Capitalize – to take advantage of an opportunity  
    Example: "We should capitalize on the growing demand for our services."
